    "For the GLUE benchmark, the models we select for fine-tuning are RoBERTa-base RoBB with 125M parameters and RoBERTa-large RoBL with 355M parameters from 68.",
    "Dropout, attention dropout, and weight decay rates are uniformly maintained at 0.2 across all tasks.",
    "The initial learning rate was 1 × 10 -4, subsequently fine-tuned to 2 × 10 -5 and 2 × 10 -6.",
    "All datasets have been trained over 10 epochs.",
    "Results: Table 1 presents a detailed performance comparison of various parameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT) methods applied to two versions of the RoBERTa model on GLUE tasks, highlighting the SK-Tuning methods as particularly effective."
